Bring a large #pot of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and quarter @zucchini{1}(quartered lengthwise); cut crosswise into ½-inch-thick pieces. Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

Once water is boiling, add @spaghetti{6%oz} to #pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}.

Reserve 1 cup pasta cooking water, then drain. (Keep empty #pot handy for step 5.)

While pasta cooks, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} in a large, preferably #nonstick pan{} over medium-high heat. Add zucchini; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and softened, ~{4-6%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate. Wipe out #nonstick pan.

Meanwhile, pat @beef tenderloin filets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @Italian seasoning{1%tbsp}, salt, and pepper.

> Swap in beef for chicken; cook to desired doneness, 4-7 minutes per side. Let rest at least 5 minutes, then thinly slice crosswise.

Once zucchini is done, heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in same nonstick pan over medium-high heat. Add beef; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest.

Once cool enough to handle, slice beef crosswise.

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in #pot used for spaghetti over medium-high heat. Add garlic, half the lemon zest, and a pinch of @chili flakes{1%tsp}. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{20-30%seconds}.

Stir in ½ cup reserved pasta cooking water (¾ cup for 4 servings), @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @sour cream{2%tbsp}, @parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}, and juice from two lemon wedges (four wedges for 4). Simmer until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Turn off heat.

Add drained spaghetti, zucchini, and @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) to #pot with sauce; toss to coat.

Add half the Parmesan and season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: If needed, stir in more reserved pasta cooking water a splash at a time until spaghetti is coated in a creamy sauce.

Divide pasta between #bowls{}. Top with beef, remaining Parmesan, remaining lemon zest, and a pinch of chili flakes if desired. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.